Description: Guild T100 T-100 D Made In The USA New Jersey Semi Acoustic Artist Guitar 1965 DeArmond Cherry Sunburst Here's a wonderful guitar that has been played loved and enjoyed. 1965 1966 from what I can date on the serial number. I have had this guitar few years she plays fine for chopping chords. guitar Pierce to be all original except for the tuning Keys which have been replaced probably sometime in the 70s. Guitar does not have any breaks or repairs that I can see. Appears to be all original wiring. Guitar was in the southern part of the United States Louisiana. Guitar has the face headstock veneer coming up. Up previous owner stated that he had always had it like that never got worse never got better. Also the action is a bit high on her not sure how much adjustment there is left on the bridge so that might be an issue for some people that want super low action. With these older guitars were made by hand so we all know the good ones don't get played. Fretz are good not sure if they've been replaced or not but they're still very playable. The guitar rings and sings and is ready to give new life into your playing. Please check out all the photographs there are dings dents scratches finish issues. Everything you could not reproduce with modern relegating. Wonderfully aged wonderfully preserve guitar with the original case. for the price of a new guitar you can buy something that's older than you are. These old gills gave Gibson a run for their money. Up until the 80s Guild really really really knew what they were doing and actually hired the Epiphone old workers prior to the purchase of epiphone. please ask as many questions as possible if there's something that's not right please let me know so I can correct it I'm no Guild expert all I know is that she's a beautiful guitar and she just doesn't get played anymore..
Title: Guild T100 T-100 D USA New Jersey Semi Acoustic Artist Guitar 1965
